# Code Review Patterns

Active code quality review during development. Not just when reviewing PRs - during ALL code work.

## Continuous Review Checklist

While reading or writing code, actively check for:

### TypeScript (src/, extensions/)
- Strict typing (no `any` unless absolutely necessary)
- ESM imports (no CommonJS require)
- Error handling (try/catch with meaningful messages, not swallowed errors)
- Null safety (optional chaining, nullish coalescing)
- File size (flag files approaching ~500-700 LOC)
- Dead code / unused imports
- Tool schema guardrails: no `Type.Union` in tool input schemas, no `anyOf`/`oneOf`/`allOf`
- Tool schema: avoid raw `format` property name (reserved keyword in some validators)

### Swift (apps/macos/, apps/ios/)
- Prefer `Observation` framework (`@Observable`, `@Bindable`) over `ObservableObject`/`@StateObject`
- Migrate existing `ObservableObject` when touching related code

### General
- No hardcoded colors (use `src/terminal/palette.ts`)
- No hand-rolled spinners (use `src/cli/progress.ts`)
- No secrets/real phone numbers/personal data in code or tests
- Brief comments for tricky logic
- Consistent naming with existing patterns

## After Reviewing Code

When you've read through code and have observations:

```
AskQuestion({
  title: "Code Review Observations",
  questions: [
    {
      id: "findings",
      prompt: "I found some things during review. Which should I address?",
      options: [
        { id: "fix-all", label: "Fix everything you found" },
        { id: "critical-only", label: "Fix critical issues only" },
        { id: "list-them", label: "List all findings and let me pick" },
        { id: "skip", label: "Skip - focus on the original task" },
        { id: "custom", label: "Other" }
      ],
      allow_multiple: false
    }
  ]
})
```

## Refactoring Opportunities

When you spot refactoring opportunities during work, always mention them. Common patterns in this codebase:
- Extract shared logic from channel implementations
- Consolidate duplicate routing/allowlist patterns across channels
- Extract CLI option patterns into shared helpers
- Unify error handling patterns
